a:3:{s:11:"notes_total";i:1;s:11:"notes_ctree";a:1:{i:0;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:36;s:5:"title";s:84:"Ergo launches “Ergo Reporting” to turn sales conversations into reportable data";s:4:"href";s:93:"http://weekcrm.com/blog/all/ergo-launches-ergo-reporting-to-turn-sales-conversations-into-re/";s:13:"href-original";s:93:"http://weekcrm.com/blog/all/ergo-launches-ergo-reporting-to-turn-sales-conversations-into-re/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1768396881;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1768396878;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:1200:"<p>Ergo (YC W25) introduced Ergo Reporting, a product it frames as revenue intelligence infrastructure based on what’s said in customer interactions, not what’s manually captured in CRM fields.</p>
<h3>What it does</h3>
<p>Ergo Reporting converts sales interactions—calls, emails, meetings, and messages—into structured data tied to outcomes. The company lists examples such as pain points, objections, competitive intel, value propositions, and deal risk extracted from conversations.</p>
<h3>How it’s meant to be used</h3>
<p>Ergo says teams can create reports on conversation-derived signals and trace insights back to the specific sentences that triggered them, aiming to explain not just what changed in pipeline, but why.</p>
<h3>What’s also included</h3>
<p>The launch also mentions a reporting agent that proactively summarizes what’s changing across a revenue team on a weekly basis.</p>
<p>Learn more: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/yash-dulla_today-ergo-yc-w25-is-announcing-the-next-activity-7415111414169755648-7TvT">https://www.linkedin.com/posts/yash-dulla_today-ergo-yc-w25-is-announcing-the-next-activity-7415111414169755648-7TvT</a></p>
